      "text": "This is the core idea of the liberal alternative to identity, but it is also the greatest liberal burden. Once the truth that bound humanity has been discarded, there is no longer a clear boundary between we-liberalism and identity politics. Once one rejects the abstract concept of humanity, Kant would have agreed with the critics of liberalism, the post-metaphysical reincarnation of a unionist politics is itself just a form of identity politics: not by black people, LGBTQ advocates, feminists, or members of other minorities, but by all those who feel comfortable starting a political debate with the phrase \"we Americans,\" \"we Germans,\" \"we Israelis.\""
